articles.content:
Class A telecommunications engineers shall possess one of the following qualifications:
Experience of more than one year with certification in the work of telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power, or telecommunications circuits. The individual shall possess one of the following additional qualifications:
Successful qualification of the Senior National Examination or Special Examination that is equivalent to the Senior National Examination in the subjects of automatic control engineering, electric power engineering, control engineering, electronics engineering, telecommunications engineering, electrical engineering, information engineering, information processing, or information science; successful qualification of the Special Professional and Technical Personnel Senior National Examination or Qualification Examination for electrical engineering, electronics engineering technician, and information technician or successful qualification of first-class, second-class or third-class Special Examination for telecommunications senior technicians;
Successful qualification of the communications business personnel upgrade examination for a telecommunications senior technician during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise;
Successful qualification of the first-class line circuit operator examination of the Special Examination for a telephone operator;
Successful qualification of the Senior National Examination or Special Examination that is equivalent to the Senior National Examination in the areas not listed in item（1）and also qualified based on the senior technician position in accordance with to the communications business personnel qualification regulations during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise.
Experience of the more than three years in the work of telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power, or telecommunications line circuits, holding certification in any of the following:
Successful qualification in electric power engineering, electronic engineering, telecommunications engineering, electrical engineering, information engineering, or information processing of the General National Examination or the forth-class Special Examination equivalent to the General National Examination, or a pass in the forth-class Special Examination for telecommunications technicians;
Successful qualification of the communications business personnel upgrade examination for telecommunications technicians during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise;
Successful qualification in the second-class line circuit operator or switchboard operator examination of Special Examination for telephone operators;
Certification in second-class or higher class telecommunications technology technician issued by the Ministry of Labor;
Successful qualification of the General National Examination or Special Examination that is equivalent to the General National Examination in the areas not listed in the item（1）of this subparagraph and also qualified based on the technician position in accordance with the regulations of communications business personnel qualification during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise.
Holding certification or a degree in telecommunications engineering, electric power engineering, electronic engineering, control engineering, information engineering or information processing, electrical engineering, information or related disciplines from a public university or private university that is legally registered for the status claimed, a college or foreign university that is recognized by the Ministry of Education, holding certification for experience of more than two years in the work of telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power or telecommunications circuits.
Having served as a telecommunications engineer in accordance with subparagraphs 3 to 8 of Article 5 of these Regulations, holding relevant certification for being engaged in the telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power or telecommunications line circuits work for more than five years.
Having served as a telecommunications engineer in accordance with subparagraph 9 and 10 of Article 5 of these Regulations, holding relevant certification for being engaged in the telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power or telecommunications line circuits work for more than eight years.

Class B telecommunications engineers shall possess one of the following qualifications:
Successful qualification of the Senior National Examination or Special Examination that is equivalent to the Senior National Examination in the subjects of automatic control engineering, electric power engineering, control engineering, electronics engineering, telecommunications engineering, electrical engineering, information engineering, or information processing, information science; successful qualification of the Special Professional and Technical Personnel Senior National Examination or Qualification Examination for electrical engineering, electronics engineering technicians, or information technicians;
Successful qualification in the area of electric power engineering, electronic engineering, telecommunications engineering, electrical engineering, information engineering, or information processing in the General National Examination or the forth-class Special Examination equivalent to the General National Examination;
Successful qualification in the level equivalent to or above of the Special Examination for telecommunications assistant technicians;
Successful qualification of the Special Examination for telephone operators;
Successful qualification in the level equivalent to or above of the communications business personnel upgrade examination for telecommunications assistant technicians during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise;
Holding certification in the third-class or higher telecommunications technology technician issued by the Ministry of Labor;
Holding certification and degree from the electronic engineering, electronic engineering, telecommunications engineering, information, information engineering, information processing, electric power engineering, control engineering or other related departments from a public or private junior college that is legally registered for the status claimed or from a foreign junior college that is recognized by the Ministry of Education or holding qualified certification from a junior college in accordance with related laws;
Successful qualification of the General National Examination or Special Examination that is equivalent to the General National Examination in the areas not listed in technical areas of subparagraphs 1 and 2 of this Article and has also qualified as a technician in accordance with the communications business personnel qualification regulations during the period working for a telecommunications enterprise;
Experience of more than three years serving as a telecommunications engineer, holding relevant certification for telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power, or telecommunications circuits work;
Holding certification from the electrical engineering, electronic engineering, electronic automatic control, control, electrical signal, electronic communications, information and related disciplines in public, private domestic skill-based senior high school or foreign skill-based senior high school that is recognized by the Ministry of Education, or holding certification from skill-based senior high school in accordance with related laws, and having relevant certification of telecommunications switching, telecommunications transmission, data communications, telecommunications electric power or telecommunications circuits work for more than three years;
Certification in Class C or above interior wire distribution, industrial wire distribution, electronic wire repair, electronic cable repair, electricity change equipment repair, electronic equipment detection category technician issued by the Ministry of Labor or class A or class B electrician with certification in accordance with laws.

The registration of telecommunication engineering enterprises shall be categorized into class A, B, and C, the operating ranges of which shall be as follows:
Class A telecommunication engineering enterprise: conducts installation, maintenance, and construction of the interconnection of the telecommunications equipment between telecommunications enterprises and of the main distribution equipment in a switching office of the telecommunications enterprise to subscribers’ terminal equipment;
Class B telecommunication engineering enterprise: conducts installation, maintenance, and construction of main distribution equipment in switching offices of telecommunications enterprises to the subscribers’ terminal equipment;
Class C telecommunication engineering enterprise: conducts installation, maintenance, and construction within the demarcation point of responsibility of the subscriber’s property.

Those that apply for registration of a Class A telecommunication engineering enterprise shall obtain the following:
Capital that exceeds TWD10,000,000;
A legal and fixed place of business;
Employs at least one telecommunications engineering personnel in the area of subparagraph 1; employs at least one telecommunications engineering personnel in the area of subparagraph 2; employs at least two  telecommunications engineering personnel in the area of subparagraph 3; telecommunications engineering personnel shall not hold the following positions in another telecommunications engineering enterprise（s）;
An electronic engineering technician, electrical engineering technician, information management technician, or personnel holding certification in a Class A communications technology category issued by the Ministry of Labor;
An electronic engineering technician, electrical engineering technician, information management technician, personnel holding certification in a Class B or above communication technology category or Class B or above network installation technician issued by the Ministry of Labor;
An electronic engineering technician, electrical engineering technician, information management technician, personnel holding certification in Class C or above communication technology category, or Class C or above network installation issued by the Ministry of Labor.

Those that apply for registration of a Class B telecommunications engineering enterprise shall obtain the following:
Capital that exceeds TWD2,000,000;
A legal and fixed place of business;
Employs at least one telecommunication engineering personnel in the area of each subparagraph 1; telecommunication engineering personnel shall not hold the following positions in another telecommunications engineering enterprise（s）,
An electronic engineering technician, electrical engineering technician, information management technician or personnel with certification in Class B or above communication technology category, or Class B or above network installation technician;
An electronic engineering technician, electrical engineering technician, information management technician, personnel with certification in Class C or above communications technology category, or Class C or above network installation.

Those that apply for the registration of telecommunications engineering enterprise shall submit the following documents to the competent authority for registration; upon successful completion of the review, the competent authority shall approve and issue a telecommunications engineering enterprise registration license:
The telecommunications engineering enterprise（s）registration license application（hereinafter as “application”）;
Photocopy of the proof of documentation of the company or commercial registration;
Photocopy of the proof of documentation of capital;
Photocopy of proof of mandatory personnel qualification documentation, a photocopy of the ID card, and employment consent letter.
The contents of the application in subparagraph 1 of the above paragraph shall include the following:
Company title, name, and its registered business office;
Company or business entity’s representative, name of the mandatory personnel, date of birth, place of residence, identity documents and document number;
Capital.
In the case where the documents submitted with the aforementioned application are deemed incomplete or deviating from regulations, the competent authority shall notify the applicant to undertake corrective action within a prescribed period of time; should the corrective action undertaken by the applicant within the prescribed period of time still be deemed incomplete, the application shall be rejected and submitted documents shall not be returned.
The application, replacement, or reissue of the telecommunications engineering enterprise（s）registration license shall be applied for online; its implementation and timetable shall be announced by the competent authority.

The license registration shall contain the following:
License number;
Name of corporation or enterprise;
Legal representative;
Capital;
Business address of corporation or enterprise;
Class of the telecommunications engineering enterprise;
Effective period.

The registration license shall be valid for a five-year period; when intending to renew the license upon expiry, the operator shall submit the following documents, three months prior to the expiry of the registration license, to the competent authority for renewal, from which the validation period begins from the following day the initial registration license expires:
The application;
Photocopy of proof of documentation of capital;
The photocopy of initial registration license;
Photocopy of proof of documentation of the company or business registration attesting that the operator’s business items include the telecommunications engineering enterprise;
The valid association member certificate.

Should there be false or fraudulent items in the application of registration of the telecommunications engineering enterprise, the competent authority shall revoke the registration.
The competent authority shall abolish the registration of the enterprise in any of the following circumstances:
The telecommunications engineering enterprise lends its license for any third party to use;
In the case of poor quality work, inferior materials, or operating construction without prior approval and has been determined by the court as endangering health or safety;
Convicted by the courts of conducting illegal bidding;
Failure to employ enough personnel within three months and failure to undertake corrective action within the prescribed period of time when notified by the competent authority when mandatory personnel resign or are laid off;
Failure to apply for resumption of its business after a period of suspension;
The operating body has been dissolved or no longer exits according to the corporation or business registration laws.
Other than the circumstances stipulated in subparagraphs 5 or 6 above, the legal representative of the telecommunications engineering enterprise whose license has been revoked or abolished, shall not be permitted to apply for registration of a telecommunications engineering enterprise within three years.
